## 4. Where You’ll See It in Real Life

| Environment                             | Purpose                          |
| --------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Cloud servers (AWS, DigitalOcean, etc.) | Web/API hosting                  |
| Enterprise backend systems              | Reverse proxy and load balancing |
| Kubernetes ingress controllers          | Traffic routing                  |
| CDNs and edge servers                   | Content caching and delivery     |
| Web dashboards (Grafana, Prometheus)    | Fronted by Nginx                 |
| Microservice architectures              | API gateway                      |

---

## 5. Difference from Router Web Server

| Feature     | Router HTTP Server   | Nginx                           |
| ----------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Scope       | Local config panel   | Internet-scale web traffic      |
| Speed focus | Small footprint      | High concurrency                |
| Hardware    | Embedded (32 MB RAM) | Server-grade (GBs of RAM)       |
| Languages   | C or Lua backend     | Any backend (C++, Node, Python) |
| Security    | Basic auth only      | HTTPS, rate limiting, WAF       |

---

### In Short

> Routers use **tiny embedded servers** for simple local management.
> Nginx is used in **servers, APIs, and cloud infrastructure** to handle **real web traffic, routing, security, and scalability**.

